transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: What is your name?

Speaker 1: Ollie speaking, Viagra School of Blue, Mr. Cardenas.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: How are we doing, Mr. Hector Cardenas?

Speaker 2: I'm doing good.

Speaker 1: I don't think I'm confused, but I received another container today.

Speaker 2: And I never asked for it.

Speaker 1: So, I think, I don't know why the guy put, I only wanted to order that one time, the first time I did.

Speaker 2: So, I just want to make sure to cancel my subscription, if there's a subscription added, because I don't know what the hell it was.

Speaker 1: But when I looked at the mail, I'm like, why are you sending me another one, when I'm the one who asked for it?

Speaker 2: So, I don't know.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: So, I put a prescription here.

Speaker 1: So, what happened was, let me, let me explain you.

Speaker 2: So, Dr. Mank wrote the prescription for Viagra AGV25 tablet, but wrote it for every, I think every two months.

Speaker 1: So, that's the initial prescription, right?

Speaker 2: Because most patients are active, and they rush, call for the Viagra, it's a whole situation, right?

Speaker 1: So, they wrote it.

Speaker 2: Oh, because I don't use it all the time.

Speaker 1: So, that's why I was like, I mean, I still have some more from, I still got a lot of them left.

Speaker 2: So, we're going to switch.

Speaker 1: We're going to switch.

Speaker 2: So, I'm going to tell you what we can do for that, because that's the initial writing, because they don't want you to have to call back, and the company got to get you a new prescription.

Speaker 1: You got to wait.

Speaker 2: You know what I'm saying?

Speaker 1: In the case you were really active, you would not like it to have to go through all of that.

Speaker 2: So, they write the prescription briefly, so it's available to you.

Speaker 1: But then now, when you don't need it, you call like you do right now.

Speaker 2: Now, we advise the pharmacy to put a pause.

Speaker 1: Mr. Cardenas is not that active.

Speaker 2: Put a pause.

Speaker 1: Don't go based on initial writing from the doctor, right?

Speaker 2: Now, if you happen to know how active you can be, you can tell me, hey, you know what, send me 10 pills or send me 25 pills in three months.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So, we can put it on hold right now?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: So, you want to hold.

Speaker 1: No, but I want to put it on hold for now completely.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So, what we do, when I advise the pharmacy, they usually pause for up to half a year to have the prescription available to you.

Speaker 2: So, it's not on a monthly basis.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's not on a monthly basis anymore.

Speaker 2: But you can reorder or get your refill once or twice a year to lock your current price in, but not every 30 days basically.

Speaker 1: Yeah, because I mean 25 is a lot of pills.

Speaker 2: You know what I mean?

Speaker 1: Yes, yes, yes.

Speaker 2: You know, if I go once every two weeks or whatever, I mean that's…

Speaker 1: And then I got another one.

Speaker 2: So, if you can put it on hold, you can put a six-month hold.

Speaker 1: I'm okay with six months.

Speaker 2: And I'll put a note on my calendar that six months from now, I will know there'll be another 25 being sent to me.

Speaker 1: And you think 25 is a good quantity for you or…

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: That's fine? Okay, perfect.

Speaker 2: Well, because that lasts me for six months, you know, it's not like I…

Speaker 1: Yes, yes.

Speaker 2: I have to call every day, you know what I mean?

Speaker 1: But yeah, I mean for six months, it should be plenty.

Speaker 2: And for some reason, if it changes, then I'll be glad to call back and say, hey…

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: You know, let's do it every four months before right now.

Speaker 1: I still have a lot from before.

Speaker 2: I just got another container to do.

Speaker 1: So, I think I'm going to be definitely okay for six months.

Speaker 2: If you can put a…

Speaker 1: Absolutely.

Speaker 2: And that way you lock your pricing.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and that way you lock your pricing.

Speaker 2: And you don't pay a new price as well when you get to refill or reorder.

Speaker 1: So, that's a good part about it.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So, I'd advise the pharmacy, you know, nothing to worry about.

Speaker 2: Deposit the prescription for you and you can reorder.

Speaker 1: In six months?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And thank you for making the time to call and let us know.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: You have a great weekend coming up and be safe, okay?

Speaker 1: You too as well.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Thank you.
